      "name": "Hemolysis model validation via published literature survey",
      "description": "A comprehensive survey of published CFD hemolysis studies for centrifugal blood pumps was conducted. Fourteen peer-reviewed publications were identified that report hemolysis index predictions using the same power-law damage model. Across these studies, the model consistently produced relative hemolysis index values within the accepted clinical range, and the aggregate findings are considered sufficient to substantiate model credibility for the CPB context of use. The literature corpus spans a range of pump geometries and operating conditions that bracket the FDA generic pump envelope, providing broad indirect corroboration of model fidelity.",
